==English==
===Etymology===
Greek very learned
===Noun===
'''polyhistor'''
#someone [[gifted]] or [[learned]] in [[multiple]] [[discipline]]s.
#a [[universal]] [[scientist]] (generally in use to describe such a person when the term [[philosophy]] meant the entire summation of all scientific [[knowledge]]; i.e., generally from the ancient Greeks into the eighteenth century.)

===Quotation===
:"(''Carlfriedrich'') Claus is an artist, though he does not like to call himself one, and a scholar.  As such, he personifies the '''polyhistor''', a species rarely found today." &mdash; [[Henry Schumann]], in ''German Art from Beckmann to Richter'', p.289.

